The opposition should stop the malicious criticism of Jubilee and focus on its mandate and issues, two leaders in West Pokot county have said.They are West Pokot Governor Simon Kachapin and Deputy Governor Titus Lotee.Kachapin said many opposition leaders are obsessed with Jubilee affairs.&ldquo;They should stop meddling in our affairs and focus on Cord or NASA issues. We want them to stop criticism of and propaganda about Jubilee,&rdquo; he said.He spoke during an inspection of development projects in Marich.Kachapin said the opposition is unable to address issues in its parties and wants to interfere with the Jubilee Party.&ldquo;We all know that NASA is going nowhere and instead of its leaders focussing on their issues, they are busy criticising President Uhuru Kenyatta and his government,&rdquo; he said.The opposition has sensed defeat at the August polls and is looking for a way of remaining relevant politically, the governor said.